---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Typenorm Media is a daily digest of UX research, product design, and AI in product."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-04-22')}
>
	<p>
		Typenorm Media is an automated digest covering UX research, product design, interaction design,
		and the role of AI in product development. Three stories publish every day — searched, written,
		and committed without manual intervention.
	</p>

	<p>
		The pipeline: <a href="https://tavily.com">Tavily</a> searches for the day's most relevant
		stories across four topic areas. Claude reads each story and writes a structured post.
		GitHub Actions runs the whole thing every morning and pushes directly to the repo.
		Vercel deploys on push.
	</p>

	<h2>Editorial policy</h2>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>Topics:</strong> UX research, product &amp; interaction design, AI in UX, design industry.</li>
		<li><strong>Audience:</strong> product designers, UX researchers, product managers, and founders who care about measurable UX outcomes.</li>
		<li><strong>Format:</strong> TL;DR → Context → Analysis → Takeaways. 300–500 words per post.</li>
		<li><strong>Style:</strong> confident, pragmatic, no fluff. Facts first — opinions labeled as such.</li>
		<li><strong>Sources:</strong> always cited. Text is never copied verbatim.</li>
	</ul>
</Layout>
